com.genologics.ri

Annotation Type GenologicsEntity


  • @Retention(value=RUNTIME)
@Target(value=TYPE)
public @interface GenologicsEntity
    Annotation to put on classes that are entities in the Clarity LIMS.

    • Required Element Summary

      Required Elements 
      Modifier and Type Required Element and Description
      String uriSection
      The part of the URL that specifies how to list or load entities of the annotated class.

    • Optional Element Summary

      Optional Elements 
      Modifier and Type Optional Element and Description
      boolean cacheable
      Whether entities of the class can be cached.
      boolean creatable
      If true, the flag indicates that entities of the annotated type can be created with a POST.
      Class<?> creationClass
      For some awkward classes that have a similar alternative class for the creation process, this attribute allows that class used in creation to be specified.
      boolean processStepComponent
      Whether the class represents parts of the process step information.
      boolean removable
      If true, the flag indicates that entities of the annotated type can be removed with DELETE.
      boolean stateful
      Whether the class represents objects that have explicit states (versions) in the Clarity system.
      boolean updateable
      If true, the flag indicates that entities of the annotated type can be updated with PUT.

    • Element Detail

      • uriSection

        public abstract String uriSection
        The part of the URL that specifies how to list or load entities of the annotated class.

        For example, the Sample class can fetch entities via the path http://blah.com/api/v2/<b>samples</b>/.... This attribute of the annotation must specify the "samples" part of the URL.

        Returns:
        The part of the URL path that yields entities of this type.

      • creatable

        public abstract boolean creatable
        If true, the flag indicates that entities of the annotated type can be created with a POST.
        Returns:
        The creatable flag.
        Default:
        false

      • updateable

        public abstract boolean updateable
        If true, the flag indicates that entities of the annotated type can be updated with PUT.
        Returns:
        The updateable flag.
        Default:
        false

      • removable

        public abstract boolean removable
        If true, the flag indicates that entities of the annotated type can be removed with DELETE.
        Returns:
        The removable flag.
        Default:
        false

      • processStepComponent

        public abstract boolean processStepComponent
        Whether the class represents parts of the process step information. These objects have an awkward URI and need to be assembled differently.
        Returns:
        The process step component flag.
        Default:
        false

      • cacheable

        public abstract boolean cacheable
        Whether entities of the class can be cached.
        Returns:
        The cacheable flag.
        Default:
        true

      • stateful

        public abstract boolean stateful
        Whether the class represents objects that have explicit states (versions) in the Clarity system. Such items will usually be returned with a "state=&lt;number&gt;" parameter in their URIs.
        Returns:
        The stateful flag.
        Default:
        false

      • creationClass

        public abstract Class<?> creationClass
        For some awkward classes that have a similar alternative class for the creation process, this attribute allows that class used in creation to be specified. The class given here needs to have a public constructor that takes a single argument of an instance of the annotated class.

        The Sample and SampleCreation classes are an example of this mechanism.

        It is prohibited in Java to assign a null as the default value of an annotation, so here the default is the class of the void type. Code using this value needs to check that that is not the value set, rather than null.

        See Also:
        Sample, SampleCreation
        Default:
        void.class
